==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|s|a}}

===Etymology===
From {{inh|fi|fiu-fin-pro|*saadak}}, from Pre-Finnic ''*sëχi-'', from Pre-Indo-Iranian ''*seģ<sup>h</sup>-''. Cognates include Swedish ''seger'', German ''sieg'', English ''school'' and ''scheme''.

===Pronunciation===
* {{fi-IPA|*}}
* {{hyphenation|saa|da|lang=fi}}
* {{rhymes|lang=fi|ɑːdɑ}}

===Verb===
{{fi-verb}}

# {{lb|fi|transitive}} to [[get]], [[receive]]
# {{lb|fi|transitive}} '''[[saada tietää]]''': to [[learn]], [[find out]], [[come]] to [[know]]
# {{lb|fi|transitive}} to [[afford]]; usually in passive {{gloss|to give forth; yield as natural result}}
#: ''Rypäleistä '''saadaan''' viiniä, oliiveista öljyä.''
#:: Grapes '''afford''' wine, olives afford oil.
# {{lb|fi|transitive|+ infinitive; in indicative or conditional mood}} to [[deserve]]
#: '''''Saisit''' hävetä!''
#:: ''You '''deserve''' to be ashamed!''
#:: ''You '''should''' be ashamed!''
# {{lb|fi|transitive|+ infinitive}} [[may]], to be [[allow]]ed, to be [[permit]]ted
# {{lb|fi|transitive|+ direct object in accusative + 3rd infinitive in illative}} to [[make]] (''to cause the direct object to be the subject of a verb'')
#: '''''Saat''' minut nauramaan.''
#:: ''You're '''making''' me laugh.''
# {{lb|fi|transitive|+ direct object in accusative + past participle in translative}} to [[get]], [[make]] something done
#: ''Oletan '''saavani''' paperit korjatuksi tänä viikonloppuna''
#:: ''I expect myself to '''get''' the papers corrected this weekend.''
# {{lb|fi|colloquial}} to [[get laid]] (If the partner is mentioned, the partner is in the [[ablative]] case (equivalent to "from"))

====Conjugation====
{{fi-conj-saada|sa|a}}

====Synonyms====
* {{sense|to deserve}} {{l|fi|sietää}} ''in indicative or conditional mood'', [[ansaita]]

